def example_ml_copilot_ws():
            # Create our client.
            client = ClientFromEnv()

            # Connect to the websocket.
            with ml_copilot_ws.WebSocket(client=client,) as websocket:

                # Send a message.
                websocket.send(MlCopilotClientMessage(OptionUser(
content="<string>",

current_files={"<string>": b"<bytes>"},

source_ranges=[SourceRangePrompt(
prompt="<string>",

range=SourceRange(

),

line=10,
),
),
)],
)))

                # Get a message.
                message = websocket.recv()
                print(message)
